body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Jenkins Solutions. My name is Michael Jenkins. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi, my name is Marilyn Lopez.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Marilyn. Can you please provide me with the last four digits of your phone number for verification purposes?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, the last four digits are eight nine two one.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. Can you also confirm the spelling of your last name?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Certainly, my last name is L-O-P-E-Z.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for the information, Marilyn. Is there anything else you would like to discuss today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all for now. Thank you.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Marilyn. Please feel free to reach out if you have any further questions. Have a great day!
